Let $G$ be the set of all continuous functions $f : RR \to RR$,
satisfying the following properties:

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")

+ $f(x) = f(x + 1)$ for all $x$,
+ $display(integral_{0}^{1} f(x) dif x = 1999)$.

Show that there is a number $alpha$ such that $alpha =
display(integral_0^1 integral_0^x f(x + y) dif y dif x)$ for all $f in G$.
